Type of firearm Springfield Model 1861 rifle musket Pattern 1853 Enfield rifle musket A rifled musket, rifle musket, or rifle-musket is a type of firearm made in the mid-19th century. Originally the term referred only to muskets that had been produced as a smoothbore weapon and later had their barrels replaced with rifled barrels.
